<subSubSection id="C374652CFF9AFFF1D4CCFE600CC1FD9A" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FF9AFFF1D4CCFE600CC1FD9A" blockId="103.[151,1436,386,701]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF9AFFF1D4CCFE600C16FE76" bold="true" box="[199,334,459,485]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Etymology.</emphasis>
The epithet is a noun in apposition honoring to the Marquetones, indigenous people who lived in the 
<collectingRegion id="49AAF845FF9AFFF1D4CBFE440CCEFD9A" box="[192,406,495,521]" country="Colombia" name="Caldas" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Caldas department</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C374652CFF9AFFF1D4CCFDB90C09FD2E" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FF9AFFF1D4CCFDB90C09FD2E" blockId="103.[151,1436,386,701]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF9AFFF1D4CCFDB90C1AFDBF" bold="true" box="[199,322,530,556]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FF9AFFF1D5BFFDB80FFFFDBF" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[436,679,531,557]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marquetones" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF9AFFF1D5BFFDB80FFFFDBF" box="[436,679,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Tenedos marquetones</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF9AFFF1D6A5FDB80FB7FDBE" bold="true" box="[686,751,531,557]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFF9AFFF1D6A5FDB80FB7FDBE" box="[686,751,531,557]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FF9AFFF1D7C7FDB80931FDBE" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[972,1129,531,557]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pensilvania" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF9AFFF1D7C7FDB80931FDBE" box="[972,1129,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">T. pensilvania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF9AFFF1D07AFDB809E9FDBE" bold="true" box="[1137,1201,531,557]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFF9AFFF1D07AFDB809E9FDBE" box="[1137,1201,531,557]" pageId="103" pageNumber="104" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, by wide retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA); large median apophysis (MA); basal tegular membrane (BTM) flattened at proximal side (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF9AFFF1D494FDF00C72FDE6" box="[159,298,603,629]" captionStart="FIGURE 73" captionStartId="103.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,725,1953]" captionTargetId="figure-165@103.[151,1436,725,1953]" captionTargetPageId="103" captionText="FIGURE 73. Tenedos marquetones sp. n. A–B. Male habits (IAvH-I-2973):A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Prolateral view. D. Retroventral. E. Ventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–F: 500µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520956/files/figure.png" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">Figs 73C–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF9AFFF1D53CFDF00CDFFDE6" box="[311,391,603,629]" captionStart="FIGURE 74" captionStartId="105.[151,250,1819,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,527,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-153@105.[151,1436,525,1796]" captionTargetPageId="105" captionText="FIGURE 74. Tenedos pensilvania sp. n. A–B. Male habits (IAvH-I-657): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Prolateral. E. Retroventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–F: 500µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520958" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520958/files/figure.png" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">74C–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF9AFFF1D59EFDF10F74FDE6" box="[405,556,602,629]" captionStart="FIGURE 75" captionStartId="106.[151,250,1438,1462]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,185,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-27@106.[151,1436,181,1415]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURE 75. Tenedos yurayaco sp. n. A, D. Male palp (IAvH-I-44):A. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. Tenedos marquetones sp. n. B, E. Male palp (IAvH-I-2973): B. Ventral view. E. Retrolateral view. Tenedos pensilvania sp. n. C, F. Male palp (IAvH- I-657): C. Ventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–F: 200µm. Abbreviations: aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; pMA, posterior branch of the median; apophysis; pRTA, posterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520960/files/figure.png" pageId="103" pageNumber="104">75A–B, D–E</figureCitation>
), but are distinguished by bifid median apophysis with squared-shaped anterior branch, short posterior branch; thinner apically tapered retrolateral tibial apophysis with apical denticles (
